definition:
A man of the tribe of Judah living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.2.47; 
 son of Caleb (H3612H) and Jahdai (H3056); 
 brother of: Regem (H7276), Jotham (H3147I), Geshan (H1529), Pelet (H6404) and Ephah (H5891I)
 § Shaaph = "division"
1) son of Jahdai of the family of Caleb, the brother of Jerahmeel
2) son of Caleb, the brother of Jerahmeel, by his concubine Maachah and father of Madmannah
